\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 They didn't get paid much did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 We
ll they never got paid while they was ; rehearsing. No, never got paid, no. There you are, that's - that's just one of them things that - that's from that - although when I went to this man for a job - I'd been in the - Angel Street bars and I'd been work
i
ng six months - on the swimming department, 'cos I used to swim a lot years ago, see. So - I was out of work and I went up and - can you like - yes, and I can swim you see. 'Cos I was only a young woman then. So he said - right, will you take on a - looki
n
g after - in the swimming department? I said, yes, all right. That was Angel Street baths. I went from there, I used to look after the - going swimming, I used to look after the - the coppers used to from Bow Street, they - they used to have their - Gala 
nights and used to swim in their - we used to have to do coffee or - whether they had beer and all that we used to have to look after 'em. Ah we've had some happy times. Yes. Never mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Your mother wasn't Irish, did she come from London?
