\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 So when your mother was at work who used to look after you two girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh my granny. Oh yes. My granny, we always had our breakfast of a morning when we went to school. My gran and grandfather.
 We always said we had two mothers and two fathers, always. Good old girl. Yes. My old grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 How many rooms were there in the house when you lived with your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh we had a six roomed house. Six roomed house in Bower Street, Lond
on Road. Oh yes. Yes, that's - that's like the - front room and the kitchen, two rooms and two at the top, yes. Granny and grandfather had the back room, me and my sister had the front, my mother and father had the back, she had the front room for her fro
nt room, my granny had that for her front near the kitchen. We all lived together. We all lived together, yes.
