alf a day, and she used to take the washing, we'd go to the baths. And one day she said to me, come on you, she said, I'll take you to the baths, so you can see - 'cos when I got in there the women said, fancy fetching her in this heat. She said, well she
'
s got to learn to do it. Well then after a time - like - my mother said, well, she said - I went to work 'til I was about - after I left school went to work - to work for me aunt and - when I was eighteen I packed up work. That's it. My mother said, well 
y
ou go to the baths and do the washing.; You look after the place here and see to the house, I'll give you so much. Which she did. Oh she was very good, yes. I did, I used to look after the house, do the washing and the ironing. She used to be a cook, and 
