\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 How serious would things have to be for someone to get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Well you - I think I was a bit saucy to her. I think so. I think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did this happen often with girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh - oh - girls and boys, yes, if they - if they were saucy or - 'cos like - well not a lot, it was only now and again you had to}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009338\charrsid1983817  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 be - you had to be - and I suppose 
I got a little bit saucy, knowing I was going to leave school at fourteen - you know, going to leave school. And having me own back on her I suppose. Well, she said, you'll go out and have the cane. 'Course I gets to the desk don't I. Oh - the head - one 
s
aid, what you - what do you want Rose? Said, I've come for the cane. 'Cos it was always the head - the head - like - mistress give us the cane. She said, what? I said, Miss Shimald sent me for the cane. She said, well what did you do? I said, I was saucy.
 
I said, I was saucy. Now, she said, you've been here all this time, now go back. And - apologise to her. 'Cos, she said, I'm not going to give you the cane. Yes. I went back. I said, I'm - she come back with me. Oh she come back. Now, she said, go on Rose
.
 I said, I'm sorry Miss Shimald. She said, all right. 'Cos it was always me - my father that was - 'cos my father said, let's hope you - like he did - you have any children of your own, if they ever - want a little bit of bread and butter always give it t
o 'em, or something like that, I don't know what - 'cos my father was - he was, he was - oh he was - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 
Did the teachers ever emphasise certain things as important, did they talk about manners being important and you had to be tidy and punctual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 
Oh we was always - we always had to be clean because there's - there used to be a nurse come and see to our heads and then they'd pull all your clothes down to see if all your vest - yes, all your vest were clean, oh we - yes, we used to - have a nurse co
me round and - examine your heads and - pull your clothes down and - if you ever got a mark you know that it was either your vest or your - well thank Gawd I never did, and I had a good mother but - never had that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 I suppose there were some children who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Lot - oh yes, yes. Oh their heads, they had to go to the - them days used to be a cleansing station they had to go. Oh yes yes. Oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 What about being punctual, were you supposed to be on time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh - always went to school - on time. My old granny always see to that. Although.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did most of the other children at your school come from a similar type of home to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Yes, some was I you know, very poor, their mums. Yes. Yes. Well I mean, my mother wasn't rich but we wer
e a bit - we - you know, we was better - really looked after than - some of the kids - children that used to - come to school, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Some were badly dressed were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh yes, oh - holes and that in their stocking - socks, oh yes, no, not like - trousers, you know, oh yes. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Would the teacher treat those any differently? Did they single them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh no, no. No, we all in the class, oh no, no. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you have any gangs or groups at your school that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 No, I don't think we ever - I don't think we ever done anything like - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Were any of the children left out of things? Or do you think most of you played together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Well we all used to really - muc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009338\charrsid1983817 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817  in together. Know what I mean, that - it's - it's funny, if we ever had any sweets - like we - you know, you - you know, give out. Well I suppose - I don't know, perhaps I was different dispos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009338\charrsid1983817 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 tion to some but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 You don't think the poorer children suffered, nobody would not play with them because they were poor or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 
No. No. No. No, 'cos you know if you - only had ha'penny or a penny you - not a penny, ha'penny them days or - a farthing comes to that, if you ever got like you - you always give 'em something, you know what I m
ean, you give 'em their bit of something or - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you ever go to any other school or was this the only school you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 No, that was the only school I went to from - when I went to school 'til I left school no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 How old were you when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 No, well it wasn't them days. That was never known them days. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you go on to any evening classes or anything after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 People left at fourteen and their education was finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Well then they went to work. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you have any regrets about your education when you look back at it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 No, I don't think so. I've always gone to work and got on all right in 
all me jobs that - well I've been in the kitchen all me life that - no, I always - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 You think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Well we used to go to - we used to go to - laundry, cookery and - all that you know, but - oh no, I suppose so,
 it - I - you know, it - it taught us - well I never had to learn any ironing or washing, me mother always see that I - see to that but - no. No, I've never regretted me - never regretted - I've always told people that I had a - happy - life as a child, y
es. When I - and when I hear some of these people, you know, terrible - like - ups and downs, fights indoors with me granny and gran - mum and all that but - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you ever have a part time job or any means of making money when you were a schoolgirl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 No. Oh no. No. Oh no. No, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 What was your first job when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 
Well let me - oh I went and worked for me aunt in Covent Garden. That's where I first was - I wanted to go in the printing line. But my mother said, well go and help your aunt out like, she'd opened a little caf\'e9
 and - go and help her out and - like after three week - two or three weeks when she gets settled, she said, I'll - I'll put you in the printing. But - come there - from - I never see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 What did you have to do in that first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh I used to - help - learn - had to - helped to cook and - clean up the - caf\'e9, I used to have to scrub the caf\'e9
 out and - like, you know, of a night and - had to work in the morning, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 What hours would you do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh well it was about - oh, I suppose eight o'clock 'til half past five. Six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 What about Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh we worked Saturdays, 'cos market was open. Yes, Saturdays 'til about - one o'clock, two o'clock and - no.
 Oh Sundays off. Holidays, all holidays like such as the market shut down, we all used to - shut down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Do you remember what you were paid in that first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 About - about six bob a week. Six bob, yes, six bob. And it was a lot of money really. Yes, six bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you think that was a fair wage at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 
Well - of course - well it was six bob was a lot of money. You could go and buy a hat for about one and eleven, two and eleven and - pair of stockings for - six three. Yes. Open worked and all that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you get any paid holidays at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 
Oh well being me aunt I mean - being me aunt - oh like - nothing like that dear. I used to say to her I was short she'd - she'd give me a few bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you give any of that money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 
No, that was mine. That's mine. No, that was mine but - although I always said, mum, can I have a new hat? She used to say, I hadn't had no wages off of you so you ain}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009338\charrsid1983817 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 t going to get a new hat. I was always one for a - new hats and - I - although my mother - my mother kept us in clothes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Even when you started working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 
Yes. Oh yes. But what - yes, we was always - me and my sister, 'cos - really there was only a - thirteen months between my sister that - really what she bought for me she bought for her that - oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 So what did you spend your six shillings on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 
Go to the pictures and - you know. Buy meself perhaps a - couple of pairs of stockings or a - can't say because - if ever I wanted anything - oh and my mothe
r used to say, all right - there used to be - Herlocks in Walworth Road was a great big like linen drapers, everything, give me sixpence a week, that goes for all your underclothes see. And - old Granny Jones in the street used to hold the clubs. Well you
 
- you'd go in it, my mum would and all that, about two or three shares, well, you used to have to - draw for it so whoever pulled - pulled out one, two, three - number three week, you - you got your - you got your club money and went to - went to - Herloc
ks and bought your underclothes and your shoes or - yes, oh yes, we always - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you like this first job, did you like working with your aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Not at first, but of course at the finish got used to it but - that - after that, well I went in 
- like after I - oh after I left her - well the war broke out didn't it and - I went to Sainsbury's I think. And - I worked at Sainsbury's. Then from there - where'd I go then? Coo -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 This is during the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh yes, I worked - in a sweet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1009338\charrsid1983817  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 stuff sh
op in London Road where I lived. During the war, because when the warning went we used to shut up and I used to go towards home and - like - you know, like - I had a young aunt and all that and I said she had a young baby, I used to get hold of him and ta
ke him down the tube. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 What were you paid at the sweetshop, can you remember? Were you paid more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 
Oh yes, I - yes, yes. Yes, I suppose about - I suppose I was about - sixteen then. I was fifteen when the war started, sixteen I suppose. I was
 there when the - the war finished, 1918, I was still there when the war finished. Yes, I had a good job there. 'Cos like - there, our guv'mor, if you like - - 'cos the war on, the - Australian soldiers used to come in, buy boxes of chocolate he used to s
a
y, well - and chocolates like was a bit hard and - some of the women used to say, come - come in, and they used to let them have chocolate for their - kiddies and all that. Soldiers used to come in with the - Australian and all that come, used to say - ge
t
 a bit extra on the boxes of chocolates you got a bonus see. Well I did to the Australians, used to fetch their girls in to buy chocolate. That's how I got me - I used to get a bonus there. I think that used to be Segars' I think he had - he had one at th
e Elephant, one in Walworth Road, one - he had five shops that man Segars. He made his money really during - during the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 What hours would you work, there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh used to be about - half past nine in the morning. 'Til about half past six at night.
 Well - no, half past six, seven, because - everybody used to come along then to go to the theatre and of course - like - well they all come in to get their sweets and - used to be all - all crowds in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Yes. Yes. Yes. I had one day off a week, that, because I worked Sundays - and I worked Saturdays but I had one day off a week for that.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 What did you think of your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh good, I - yes, I had a - I had a - missus and guv'nor had one daughter, they treated me like their - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you quite like this work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh I enjoyed it 'cos there was - all the sweets, weighing up and - it was interesting really. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid752558 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Did you get any holidays through that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8213171 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10178391\charrsid1983817 Oh yes, oh weeks holiday, a weeks holiday.
