nd me was she. Yes, she started work when she was fourteen at - Sainsbury's. And she worked there 'til she - got married, she worked there, she got married when she was - twenty-one. And of course at Sainsbury's years ago, once you got married you couldn'
t
 be - you couldn't go to work, never - they never employed married women. Yes, Sainsbury's in - in Stamford Street. Yes. Yes. No, no. No, didn't - well you know it now. No. Yes, that' was Sainsburys. My sister packed up work when she got married, I think 
s
he was twenty-one, she got married in the Christmas. Now let me see, no, she was a bit older than twenty-one I think. Any old how, that day - that week when she was getting married she got her cards. Yes, that's Sainsbury's. And when we used to work there
 
